  "text": "Firefox crashes when processing CSS calc() expressions with extreme numeric values due to how overflow and infinity/NaN are handled. The primary code path involves:\n\n1. **CSS calc() Parsing** (servo/components/style/values/specified/calc.rs):\n   - The `MathFunction` enum defines all CSS math functions (calc, min, max, clamp, round, mod, rem, etc.)\n   - The `Leaf` enum represents AST leaf nodes (Length, Angle, Time, Resolution, Percentage, Number, etc.)\n   - CSS calc expressions are parsed into an abstract syntax tree of these types\n\n2. **Generic Calc Node Implementation** (servo/components/style/values/generics/calc.rs):\n   - `CalcNode` and `GenericCalcNode` define the tree structure with operations (Sum, Product, MinMax, Clamp, Round, ModRem, etc.)\n   - Critical overflow/infinity handling in `ModRemOp::apply()` (lines 65-87): Special handling for mod() with infinite divisors; if divisor is infinite and dividend has opposite sign, returns NaN\n   - `CalcNode::resolve()` and `resolve_internal()` (lines 916-1046+) resolve calc expressions to final values, handling infinity/NaN propagation through arithmetic operations\n   - `CalcNodeLeaf` trait methods:\n     - `is_infinite()`, `is_nan()`, `is_negative()`, `is_zero()`: Check for special numeric states\n     - `try_sum_in_place()`, `try_product_in_place()`: Merge leaves with overflow/infinity checks\n     - `coerce_to_value()`: Replace node values with infinity or NaN (used in round() function with infinite step values, lines 1396-1456)\n   - Round function handling with infinite step values: When step is infinite, specific rounding strategies determine if result becomes infinity, zero, or NaN (lines 1414-1457)\n\n3. **Typed OM CSS Math Classes** (layout/style/typedom/CSSMath*.cpp/h):\n   - `CSSNumericValue` base class provides DOM API for numeric values\n   - `CSSMathSum`, `CSSMathProduct`, `CSSMathMin`, `CSSMathMax`, `CSSMathClamp` implement corresponding CSS math functions\n   - `CSSMathSum::Create()` and similar methods handle creation from Servo style values\n   - Arithmetic operations (Add, Sub, Mul, Div, Min, Max) throw NS_ERROR_NOT_IMPLEMENTED for now (CSSNumericValue.cpp lines 60-94)\n\n4. **Numeric Value Handling** (servo/components/style/typed_om/):\n   - `numeric_values.rs`: Defines `NoCalcNumeric` enum for length and percentage values without calc\n   - `sum_value.rs`: `SumValue` struct represents CSS numeric sums with unit tracking for validation\n\nThe crash likely occurs in the interaction between infinite/NaN propagation in `resolve_internal()` and the special handling of extreme values in `ModRemOp::apply()` or rounding operations with infinite step values. The code correctly implements infinity/NaN semantics per CSS Typed OM specifications, but edge cases with extreme value combinations may trigger unsafe memory access or algorithmic errors."
}

